1) Root cause confirmation (alerts/events/logs)

- Alert: `NodeDiskPressure` on `worker-node-03`, source `data-sync-job`, with ephemeral storage at `87%`.
- Events:
  - `Warning / DiskPressure`: `Pod data-sync-job-pod is using 85% of node ephemeral storage on worker-node-03`
  - `Warning / UnusualLogVolume`: `Pod data-sync-job-pod produced 42GB of log output in the last 6 hours`
  - Cluster event: `Node worker-node-03 has insufficient ephemeral storage`
- Logs from `data-sync-job` confirm the failure mode:
  - `Write buffer overflow - spilling to disk at /tmp/sync-buffer-4721.log`
  - `Failed to write buffer: No space left on device`
  - `FATAL Sync process aborted: storage full`

Conclusion: the job’s uncontrolled log/output buffering filled ephemeral storage and triggered the node disk pressure alert.

2) Why the job is the stray test job (owner/purpose/labels)

- `owner`: `test-developer`
- `purpose`: `data synchronization test`
- `labels`:
  - `environment: test`
  - `managed-by: manual-test`
  - `app: data-sync`

This matches the runbook’s stray test-job signature, not the production workload (`owner: platform-team`). The running pod was also directly tied to this job: `data-sync-job-pod` on `worker-node-03`.

